1. Explain about Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps is a low-code/no-code platform from Microsoft that enables rapid development of custom business apps.

ğŸ‘‰ It supports building apps that connect to various data sources like Dataverse, SharePoint, and SQL with minimal coding effort.

ğŸ‘‰ Canvas Apps are primarily used to design rich, interactive user interfaces and implement business logic through Power Fx formulas.

ğŸ‘‰ Integration with Power Automate allows automation of workflows such as approvals, notifications, and real-time record updates.

ğŸ‘‰ The core objective is to simplify and accelerate app development for internal business needs, reduce manual work, and drive productivity improvements.

âœ… Summary Note:
ğŸ‘‰ Power Apps (Canvas and Model-Driven) are for internal business use only and cannot be used to create truly public-facing apps.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Features of Power Apps:
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1. Low-Code Development    : Drag-and-drop interface allows building apps without deep coding knowledge.

2. Data Connectivity       : Connects to 500+ data sources like SharePoint, Dataverse, SQL, Excel, and custom APIs using connectors.

3. Responsive Design       : Apps work on mobile, tablet, and desktop automatically.

4. Integration with Power Automate  : Easily triggers workflows for automation â€” like sending emails or approvals.

5. Prebuilt Templates and Controls  : Offers ready-made templates, galleries, forms, and reusable components for faster development.

6. Offline Capability      : Apps can store data locally and sync when connected â€” useful for field workers.

7. AI Builder Support      : Use AI to extract text, predict outcomes, or process forms without writing machine learning models.

8. Role-Based Security     : Control who can view, edit, or submit data using role-based permissions and Microsoft Dataverse security.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Difference between Canvas App and Model-Driven App?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1ï¸âƒ£ Canvas Apps:
ğŸ‘‰ Canvas Apps Provide full flexibility control over app layouts and UI built from scratch using a blank canvas app. 
ğŸ‘‰ The design process using drag-and-drop components like buttons, galleries, forms and more.
ğŸ‘‰ We can Connect easily to various data sources such as SharePoint, Excel, SQL, and Dataverse.
ğŸ‘‰ use Power Fx formulas to drive business logic and interactivity.

2ï¸âƒ£ Model-Driven Apps:
ğŸ‘‰ Model-driven apps are based on the data model in Dataverse.
ğŸ‘‰ The UI is generated automatically based on the data model â€”tables, relationships, forms, and views.
ğŸ‘‰ so we donâ€™t have to build the UI manually like in canvas apps.
