4. Collections and types of Collections in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Collections act as temporary in-memory tables used to store data within the app session.
ğŸ‘‰ Theyâ€™re particularly useful for managing user inputs, maintaining app state, and enabling offline functionality.
ğŸ‘‰ Functions like Collect, ClearCollect, and Clear are commonly used to create, update, and reset collections.
ğŸ‘‰ Collections help optimize performance by caching data locally and minimizing frequent calls to external data sources, 
    especially when working with multiple records.

ğŸ”¹ Types of Collections:
1. Collect() function: Creates a new collection or adds records to an existing one.
âœ… Example: Collect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice", Age: 25}) or using input controls like {Name: TextInput.Text, Age: Value(TextInput.Text)}

2. ClearCollect() function: Clears all existing records from a collection and adds new records in one step.
âœ… Example: ClearCollect(MyCollection, {Name: "Alice1", Age: 20})

3. Clear() function: Removes all records from a collection, effectively emptying it.
âœ… Example: Clear(MyCollection)
