6. Cascading Dropdown in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ Cascading Dropdown is a pair of dropdown controls where the options in the child dropdown,
    dynamically depend on the selection made in the parent dropdown.

âœ… For example, a Countryâ€“City scenario:
Dropdown 1 (Country) ---------> Items property: Distinct(CountriesCities, Country)
Dropdown 2 (City) ------------> Items property: Filter(CountriesCities, Country = Dropdown1.Selected.Result)

ğŸ‘‰ So, when a user selects a country, only cities related to that country appear in the second dropdown.
