16. How do you create a Responsive Design in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ To make apps responsive Design in Power Apps, I use container controls like vertical and horizontal containers based on the requirements.
ğŸ‘‰ These containers automatically arrange the elements inside them based on the screen size.
ğŸ‘‰ Instead of fixing the size and position of each control, I use formulas that adjust their width and height relative to the screen.
âœ… For Example:
ğŸ‘‰ We can use relative properities like parent.width and parent.height to adjust sizes and positions dynamically.
ğŸ‘‰ This approach lets the app look good on any device â€” whether itâ€™s a phone, tablet, or desktop, without having to create separate versions.
